.TH unix_telnet 3 "common_test 1.30" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
unix_telnet \- Callback module for \fIct_telnet\fR, for connecting to a Telnet server on a UNIX host.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
It requires the following entry in the configuration file:

.IP
.nf
{unix,[{telnet,HostNameOrIpAddress},
       {port,PortNum},                 % optional
       {username,UserName},
       {password,Password},
       {keep_alive,Bool}]}.            % optional

.fi

.PP
To communicate through Telnet to the host specified by \fIHostNameOrIpAddress\fR, use the interface functions in \fIct_telnet\fR, for example, \fIopen(Name)\fR and \fIcmd(Name,Cmd)\fR.

.PP
\fIName\fR is the name you allocated to the Unix host in your \fIrequire\fR statement, for example:

.IP
.nf
suite() -> [{require,Name,{unix,[telnet]}}].

.fi

.PP
or

.IP
.nf
ct:require(Name,{unix,[telnet]}).

.fi

.PP
The "keep alive" activity (that is, that \fICommon Test\fR sends NOP to the server every 10 seconds if the connection is idle) can be enabled or disabled for one particular connection as described here. It can be disabled for all connections using \fItelnet_settings\fR (see \fIct_telnet\fR).

.PP
The \fI{port,PortNum}\fR tuple is optional and if omitted, default Telnet port 23 is used. Also the \fIkeep_alive\fR tuple is optional, and the value default to \fItrue\fR (enabled).

.PP
\fBSee Also\fR

.PP
\fIct\fR, \fIct_telnet\fR

.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBconnect(ConnName, Ip, Port, Timeout, KeepAlive, TCPNoDelay, Extra) ->\fR
\fB                 {ok, Handle} | {error, Reason}\fR
\fB                 when\fR
\fB                     ConnName :: ct:target_name(),\fR
\fB                     Ip :: inet:socket_address() | inet:hostname(),\fR
\fB                     Port :: inet:port_number(),\fR
\fB                     Timeout :: timeout(),\fR
\fB                     KeepAlive :: boolean(),\fR
\fB                     TCPNoDelay :: boolean(),\fR
\fB                     Extra :: {Username, Password} | KeyOrName,\fR
\fB                     Username :: iodata(),\fR
\fB                     Password :: iodata(),\fR
\fB                     KeyOrName :: ct:key_or_name(),\fR
\fB                     Handle :: ct_telnet:handle(),\fR
\fB                     Reason :: term().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Callback for \fIct_telnet.erl\fR.

.PP
Setup Telnet connection to a Unix host.


.RE
.B
\fBget_prompt_regexp() -> Pattern\fR
\fB                           when Pattern :: ct_telnet:prompt_regexp().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Callback for \fIct_telnet.erl\fR.

.PP
Returns a suitable \fIregexp\fR string matching common prompts for users on Unix hosts.


.RE
